[GPU]
Sims2Warning=Do NOT apply this patch if you are running the Legacy Collection of Sims 2, as it is no longer required with the latest release of the new Legacy Collection. DO patch if you are running Retail or Complete Collection editions.
Sims2Title=Graphics Rules Maker — The Sims 2

[Tweaks]
AlderLake_Info1=On the newest Core i3-i9, 12th gen Intel Alder Lake CPU, The Sims 3 crashes upon starting. This fix will allow users with Alder Lake CPU's to be able to play the game again. The Ultimate ASI Loader & Sims 3 Settings Setter also solve this issue as well.
AlderLake_Info2=If you are running the EA App version of The Sims 3, this fix is no longer required as it has been fixed in v1.69.47.024017 (01/13/2025). Users running the Retail or Steam versions of the game will still need to use this patch to run the game on newer Intel CPU's.
AlderLake_Title=Intel Alder Lake Fix — The Sims 3
AlderLake_ExtractFail=Failed to extract Alder Lake patch:\n{0}
AlderLake_NotFound=Extraction succeeded but AlderLakePatch.exe could not be found in your Sims 3 directory.
LDLauncher_Info1=A custom TS3 Launcher for the EA App (version 1.69), allowing for greater control. Features ASI mod support, launcher bypass, show all EP's, better SimPort login & disable all CC.
LDLauncher_Info2=For EA App only. By default, this installer extracts to the default path and will replace the game's vanilla launcher. If you have installed The Sims 3 elsewhere, you will need to manually change the install location.
LDLauncher_Title=LazyDuchess Launcher — The Sims 3
LDLauncher_BackupFail=Could not back up the existing Sims3Launcher.exe:\n{0}\n\nThe installation will not proceed.
MonoPatcher_Info1=Another amazing mod by LazyDuchess, Mono Patcher is a library that allows Script Modders to replace Sims 3 methods with as much compatibility as possible - No need to create core mods anymore to replace game functions.
MonoPatcher_Info2=Current Version: 0.2.2
MonoPatcher_Title=Mono Patcher Library — The Sims 3
MonoPatch_Info1=Mono Patcher is a library that allows Script Modders to replace Sims 3 methods with as much compatibility as possible - No need to create core mods anymore to replace game functions.
MonoPatch_Info2=Mono Patcher is required for some of the mods featured by SimTools. It's installation is highly suggested.
MonoPatch_Title=LazyDuchess Mono Patcher — The Sims 3
PatchDL_Info1=INFO: You should only need to update to 1.67 if you are running the game from the Retail discs. EA App and Steam versions will already be updated to the latest versions when installed.
PatchDL_Info2=Use the following Patch Downloader to download patches for the base game and expansions you have installed.
PatchDL_Info3=Furthermore, it is highly recommended that you patch each title after you have installed it. As an example, install base game, patch it, install World Adventures, patch it, and so on and so forth.
PatchDL_Title=Patch Downloader — The Sims 3
Simler90_Info=Simler90's Gameplay Systems Core Mod fixes a long list of issues and bugs with the base game and many of the expansion packs. STRONGLY recommended.
Simler90_Title=Simler90's Fixes — The Sims 3
GameplayFixes_Info=Launching Game Fixes AIO installer. Select fixes ONLY for the expansions that you have installed.
GameplayFixes_Title=Gameplay Fixes — The Sims 3
SimCopterX_Info=This is an alert from central dispatch - you're cleared for takeoff on Windows 10. You no longer need to use a virtual machine or CPU Killer, just nerves of steel. Additionally the patcher has optional higher-resolution modes to choose from including 16:9 and 16:10 aspect ratios so you can fill up your screen; you'll feel like you're actually up in the sky saving shipwrecked Sims.
SimCopterX_Title=SimCopterX
SimStreetsX_Info=Take your rage to the streets on Windows 10 by becoming a lunatic Sim driver. You no longer need to use a virtual machine or CPU Killer, just a lead foot. The patcher comes with a variety of options so you can either take a relaxing drive or battle up to seven other players over a network.
SimStreetsX_Title=SimStreetsX
SC2kFix_Info=SC2KFix is a bugfix and modding plugin for SimCity 2000 Special Edition. Compatible with the Windows 95 version only. Use alongside SC2000X is untested.
SC2kFix_Title=SC2kFix — SimCity 2000
SC2000X_Info=SC2000X is an open-source installer and patcher for SimCity 2000 (Win95). In addition to being an all-in-one solution, it's completely open source and supports multiple versions of the game. The patcher fixes the “Save-As” crash bug, which is actually a general dialog bug extending to “Load Tile Set” as well.
SC2000X_Title=SC2000X — SimCity 2000

[BugFixes]
Sims1_Info=Please use Simitone under Game Tweaks to address The Sims 1 game bugs.
Sims1_Title=The Sims 1 — Bug Fixes
Sims4_Info=To be implemented at a later time.
Sims4_Title=The Sims 4 — Bug Fixes
ShadowFix_Info=With this mod, Sims' and pets' indoor shadows no longer appear as black rectangles. This problem occurs on many modern graphics cards.
ShadowFix_Title=Sim Shadow Fix — The Sims 2
BrightCAS_Info=This mod fixes CAS parts that were made without Bump Map support looking glowy in CAS, or nearly everything being glowy for people playing with shaders disabled. LazyDuchess FTW!
BrightCAS_Title=Bright CAS Fix — The Sims 2

